DE  Decarboxylation/antiport proton-motive cycle: tyrosine-tyramine
TP  SYSTEM
AU  Haft DH
TH  0
RN  [1]
RM  12089039
RT  Identification of the Enterococcus faecalis tyrosine decarboxylase
RT  operon involved in tyramine production.
RA  Connil N, Le Breton Y, Dousset X, Auffray Y, Rincé A, Prévost H;
RL  Appl Environ Microbiol. 2002;68:3537-3544.
CC  The decarboxylation of tyrosine to tyramine consumes a proton. Exchange
CC  of tyrosine for tyramine by an antiporter completes a cycle that
CC  effectively removes a cytosolic proton. Decarboxylation/antiporter
CC  systems for this and other (e.g. aspartate-alanine) substrate pairs can
CC  provide protection against acidic pH.  
